verbose_text: A re-classification of CLC classes was applied to produce the urban-rural map of the Test 4 areas : Urban areas include all the CLC artificial surfaces (namely continuous and discontinuous urban fabric, industrial and commercial units, construction sites, green urban areas and sport-leisure facilities), while rural areas group all the elements inventoried by CLC as agricultural, or forest and semi-natural land use.
evidence: CLC classes was applied to produce the urban-rural map
